title: Dominican Republic Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Dominican Republic increased 9.90 percent in October of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Dominican Republic averaged 9 percent from 2000 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 94.54 percent in March of 2004 and a record low of -9.87 percent in August of 2005. This page provides - Dominican Republic Food Inflation - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of Dominican Republic
